Sentencas: Degradation suffering from ambient water vapor in air is harmful for cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), it is necessary and important to research its attenuation mecha- nism and related preventive methods.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-delta (STC) cathode have been discussed in detailed.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction analysis reveals that STC is relatively stable in wet air with a little crystal contraction, but without obvious impurities.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Because active sites of STC for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) are covered by water vapor, the electrical conductivity decreases while the polarization resistance (R-p) increases with the increasing of the water vapor concentration in air.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with R-p measured in dry air, the enhanced R-p value is 0.0347 Omega cm(2) and 0.0493 Omega cm(2) in containing 3% and 5% H2O air after a continuous testing for 96 h at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, a maxium power densities of 832 mW cm(-2) and 814 mW cm(-2) can be obtained for STC/LSGM/STC in dry air and containing 5% H2O air after 96 h operating at 800 degrees C, respecctively.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Interestingly, the degradation coming from humidity can be recovered partially by switching the feedgas back to dry air again.
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The R-p of STC becomes -0.0402 c cm(2) again after switching the operating atmosphere from 5% H2O air to dry air for 5 h. (C) 2020
Titulo: Effects of humidity on SrTi0.05Co0.95O3-δ cathode properties and durability of solid oxide fuel cells
